1
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:34,200
Do you mean

2
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:38,480
you're going to find such a huge bluestone slab?

3
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,240
No, I'm not.

4
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,680
The reason I'm telling you this

5
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,200
is to make you understand

6
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:56,120
our ancestors weren't stubbornly conservative

7
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:58,400
or rigidly unchanging.

8
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,520
They adapted.

9
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:03,320
So clever, so wise.

10
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:06,320
They found solutions through change.

11
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,960
They wouldn't just push forward blindly.

12
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,200
Zhang Du.

13
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:19,160
How long have you been here?

14
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:23,360
One year and eight months.

15
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,720
As the old saying goes,

16
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:28,640
three years an apprentice, five years competent,

17
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,520
seven years a master.

18
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:31,600
Look at you.

19
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,080
You haven't been here long,

20
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,760
but you're already the Chief Papermaker.

21
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,200
You've even been on TV.

22
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,200
You're far better than I was.

23
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,440
You've got a bright future.

24
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,760
How could I ever compare to you?

25
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,040
Please don't tease me.

26
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,200
You, as a person,

27
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,800
are smart and hardworking.

28
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,800
Really impressive.

29
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:01,320
But when it comes to conduct and work,

30
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:05,280
you have to be like making paper.

31
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,800
108 steps,

32
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:12,440
taken one solid step at a time.

33
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,800
Don't you think in the Xuan Family now,

34
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,840
I'm the most grounded of them all?

35
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,520
From the day I joined the Xuan Family until now,

36
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,520
every hard and tiring job,

37
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,000
I've always been the first to take on.

38
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,280
I haven't slacked off for a single day.

39
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,400
Don't get worked up.

40
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,360
I'm not, Master.

41
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,760
Yes, they don't like me.

42
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:35,440
Because our philosophies differ.

43
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,880
That I can understand.

44
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,080
But look at how much I've done.

45
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,720
Master, you've seen it all.

46
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,400
Everything I've done

47
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,760
is to bring glory to the Xuan family.

48
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,560
I know, I know.

49
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,080
All the hard work you've put in,

50
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,480
I see it clearly.

51
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,000
Master.

52
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,840
Since you just brought it up,

53
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:04,600
there's something I've been wanting to say.

54
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,160
Just say it.

55
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,400
Go on, I'm listening.

56
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:15,200
A thousand-year Xuan Family, a thousand-year legacy.

57
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,360
So as the Xuan Family paper mill,

58
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:21,079
we must stick to the ancient methods.

59
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,200
Go on.

60
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,920
Return to simplicity.

61
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:32,800
That's what many modern people pursue.

62
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:36,640
Reviving and preserving the ancient methods

63
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:39,080
not only produces excellent paper,

64
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,600
it's also a huge selling point.

65
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,720
The tougher things get,

66
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,080
the more we need to stay true to ourselves.

67
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,120
That's really about upholding the Xuan Family brand.

68
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,560
I stand by tradition,

69
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,160
but I stand by innovation even more.

70
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,480
Generations of the Xuan Family

71
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:01,440
have carried on through constant refinement and progress.

72
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,280
That's how the legacy survived.

73
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,680
Why do I keep telling you

74
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,000
to stay grounded?

75
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,880
Wanting to make good paper is fine.

76
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,040
That's right.

77
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,640
But when you're making paper,

78
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,960
if you're also thinking about marketing,

79
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,280
and how to sell it,

80
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,560
and all those honors,

81
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,320
you're thinking too much.

82
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,440
Then the paper won't turn out well.

83
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,640
When I'm making paper,

84
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,480
I don't think about all that.

85
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,480
Alright.

86
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,160
Head back and get some rest.

87
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,680
It's the first time I've seen you

88
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,880
so unsure about our own paper.

89
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,360
Who says I'm unsure?

90
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,360
If I were, would I be going to Beijing?

91
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:30,760
The tickets are booked.

92
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,200
Young Lin helped me buy them.

93
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,240
At the station,

94
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,400
I just swipe my ID and I'm in.

95
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:37,920
Just look at that.

96
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:40,000
Society's moving so fast these days,

97
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,560
we can't even buy a train ticket anymore.

98
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,760
Lucky we have Miss Lin around,

99
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,560
handling everything at home so well.

100
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,440
Someone in our own family knows how,

101
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:55,800
but he's nowhere to be seen for days on end.

102
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,640
Worse than an outsider.

103
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,640
Then treat Miss Lin as family,

104
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,680
not as an outsider.

105
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,680
Am I that lucky?

106
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,200
Alright, enough.

107
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,440
Stop fussing around here.

108
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,680
Go pack your things.

109
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,440
Get ready.

110
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,560
You're heading to Beijing.

111
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,160
I've got things covered here.

112
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:14,640
Go on, go on.

113
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,120
Alright, alright.

114
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,120
Be thorough now.

115
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,520
Master,

116
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,520
for last year's Ancestral Worship Ceremony,

117
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,680
we prepared a pig's head and chicken,

118
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,680
along with many other things.

119
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,280
The date's drawing near, I see.

120
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,160
Shouldn't we

121
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,520
start getting ready too?

122
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,000
Right now, everyone here

123
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,640
is going all out

124
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,880
preparing to enter Pine and Crane Studio.

125
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:00,640
As for this year's Ancestral Worship Ceremony,

126
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,720
I say let's put it on hold.

127
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,960
We'll wait until next year

128
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,760
to hold the ceremony.

129
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,680
A delay wouldn't hurt.

130
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:14,120
After all, this year

131
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,240
is just too rushed.

132
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,080
Well, you get back to work.

133
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:18,680
I'm heading back.

134
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,320
Alright.

135
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:31,040
If you don't want to drink with me,

136
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,880
I'll go make you some tea.

137
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,760
Don't bother.

138
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:35,240
I've been drinking water all night.

139
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,559
If there's nothing else, I'm heading back.

140
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,559
I still have paperwork to finish.

141
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,559
Yiran, Yiran, Yiran.

142
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,200
Sit with me a little longer.

143
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,760
Just for a moment.

144
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,760
Come on.

145
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,040
Alright, I'll do it myself.

146
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,240
Here, please have a seat.

147
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,320
So tell me,

148
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,640
go on, tell me.

149
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,880
Is the Ancient-method paper I want to make better,

150
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,760
or the traditional handmade paper the Xuan Family makes now?

151
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,240
Come on, Zhang Du,

152
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:59,040
I don't know anything about this.

153
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,760
You're so clever, of course you know.

154
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,560
No.

155
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,040
How would I know?

156
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:03,920
I don't know a thing.

157
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,440
I don't know anything. I'm dumb as a rock.

158
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,560
You're not only clever,

159
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,240
you're wise too.

160
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,080
Listen to you talk.

161
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:14,200
I might as well go home and look in the mirror.

162
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,880
All I've ever wanted

163
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:19,360
is to restore the Xuan Family's thousand-year glory.

164
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:21,360
For a thousand years, the Xuan Family

165
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,520
has been making Ancient-method paper.

166
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,680
I'm inheriting a thousand-year tradition.

167
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,200
Is that wrong?

168
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,760
Honestly,

169
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,680
I really admire you.

170
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,760
But sadly,

171
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,880
the Xuan Family doesn't see it that way.

172
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:48,320
Why not put yourself in his shoes?

173
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,400
Uncle Xuan sticks to his views so firmly.

174
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,760
Maybe he has his reasons.

175
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,160
No.

176
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,520
I'm an outsider.

177
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,080
My surname isn't Xuan.

178
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,760
Alright, stop drinking.

179
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,880
You've had enough.

180
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,440
Hurry home and get some rest.

181
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,760
I should head back too.

182
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,640
I just want to tell you,

183
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:10,760
if I were Xuan Yan,

184
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,280
my persistence wouldn't be wrong.

185
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,560
Well, let me tell you, that's just what you think.

186
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,400
In his father's eyes, Xuan Yan is dead wrong.

187
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,240
You know that?

188
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,160
Wait a second.

189
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:26,760
Hold on.

190
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:46,960
They laugh at my madness,

191
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:51,160
I laugh at their blindness.

192
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,880
The heroes' tombs are gone,

193
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,280
now fields tilled

194
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:02,200
without flower or wine.

195
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,000
Stop watching.

196
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,880
Watching won't let you scoop paper.

197
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,960
You're one of a kind now.

198
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:45,720
Just these few people, just this bit of work.

199
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,480
What else are you worried about?

200
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,240
That's not what I meant.

201
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,000
What I mean is,

202
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,480
I'm heading to Beijing soon.

203
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,840
Nothing can go wrong here at home.

204
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:00,880
Xiaoman.

205
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,240
Master.

206
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,840
Why isn't Zhang Du scooping paper with you?

207
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,760
He didn't come in today.

208
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,760
I called him.

209
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:08,960
He said he wasn't feeling well.

210
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:09,880
Asked for a day off.

211
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,760
It's not that he's feeling unwell.

212
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,520
He's upset inside.

213
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:21,360
We all work together year-round like family.

214
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,320
Don't gossip behind people's backs.

215
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,240
That's not right.

216
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,720
Listen, everyone.

217
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,000
This trip to Beijing,

218
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:31,760
I'll be gone for several days.

219
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,160
Everyone needs to stay alert.

220
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,840
What does our trade fear most?

221
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,040
Fire, fire, fire!

222
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:38,400
Right.

223
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,360
We can't afford to touch fire.

224
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,000
One spark and disaster strikes.

225
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,360
The quality is exceptional.

226
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,520
Really smooth.

227
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,680
And there's this one too.

228
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:28,640
Better value for money.

229
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,560
Five hundred eighty.

230
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,720
If it's meant as a gift,

231
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:34,240
I'd suggest pairing it with a stack of Xuan paper.

232
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:34,800
Take a look.

233
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,040
This Xuan paper of ours,

234
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:36,880
it's really top quality.

235
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,920
Right, and over there too.

236
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,400
Have a look around first.

237
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,280
Hello, sir.

238
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,640
Hello, hello.

239
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,000
How may I help you?

240
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:49,480
I'm here to discuss a partnership.

241
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,360
You'd need to speak with our purchasing department.

242
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:53,720
Do you have an appointment?

243
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,680
Could you please pass along a message?

244
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,120
Tell them the Xuan Family of Jing County

245
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:02,120
has been partnering with Pine and Crane Studio

246
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,160
for centuries, since the Kangxi era.

247
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,680
I'm here today to discuss resuming our partnership.

248
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,400
All right.

249
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:10,680
Please wait a moment.

250
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,680
Sir,

251
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,920
you came from Jing County?

252
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:43,680
Yes, yes.

253
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:45,640
Please, have a seat.

254
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:46,560
Bring some tea.

255
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,640
I'm quite busy.

256
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,120
Let's get straight to the point.

257
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:51,960
Alright, alright.

258
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:55,400
I'm from Jing County, Xuancheng.

259
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,640
My name is Xuan Yongnian.

260
00:14:57,560 --> 00:15:00,600
The 35th-generation heir of Xuan Family paper.

261
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:03,400
And an ICH Inheritor of Chinese Xuan paper.

262
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,720
Please, take a look at this.

263
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,240
Have some tea first.

264
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,680
Thank you, no need.

265
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:18,920
Take a look.

266
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,480
This is Xuan Family Xuan paper.

267
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,840
No need, no need.

268
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,680
These here

269
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:33,040
are papers for Pine and Crane Studio.

270
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,800
These are all handmade papers.

271
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,400
Fine paper, fine paper.

272
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,160
Indeed.

273
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,280
The Xuan Family has been making Xuan paper

274
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,320
since the Song Dynasty.

275
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,240
Blue sandalwood bark and sand-field rice straw

276
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,240
originated from our Xuan Family.

277
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:49,840
Over a thousand years of history.

278
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:51,400
Pine and Crane Studio

279
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,680
made its name back in the Kangxi era.

280
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,600
All the way to the Republic era,

281
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,600
they used our Xuan Family paper.

282
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,760
I've heard of it, I've heard of it.

283
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,840
Mr. Xuan, just call me Xiao Xu.

284
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,640
I'm in charge of Xuan paper purchasing.

285
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,360
Here's the thing, Mr. Xuan.

286
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,160
We already have partner suppliers,

287
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:14,120
and it's very stable.

288
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,120
For many years now.

289
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,280
I know.

290
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,640
We've been working together for nearly a century.

291
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:21,760
But that's all in the past, isn't it?

292
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,000
After cooperating for so long,

293
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,120
we can keep cooperating just as well going forward.

294
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,160
Mr. Xuan, Mr. Xuan.

295
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,280
Didn't I just say?

296
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:36,240
We have long-term, stable partner suppliers,

297
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,680
and the cooperation has been excellent.

298
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,360
Manager Xu, don't misunderstand.

299
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:45,360
I have absolutely no intention of stealing anyone's business.

300
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,880
What I mean is, whether paper sells well or not,

301
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,280
quality is what matters most.

302
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:53,480
Let the quality speak for itself.

303
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,000
Please take a look.

304
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,480
See what you think of the quality.

305
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,000
If it's not good enough,

306
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,360
if the quality doesn't pass muster,

307
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,600
I'll turn around and leave without another word.

308
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,400
Just take a look.

309
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:05,680
Come, come, come.

310
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,480
Give me a hand.

311
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:09,640
Have a look.

312
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:13,240
Light as cicada wings, white as snow,

313
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:16,400
silent as silk when shaken,

314
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,000
ink spreads like clouds in five shades,

315
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,960
and colors stay fresh for ages without decay.

316
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:25,520
Mr. Xuan, how about this?

317
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,680
Leave the paper here,

318
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,920
leave your contact info,

319
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:29,880
head back home,

320
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:33,040
and we'll get in touch by phone.

321
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:33,800
Sound good?

322
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,040
Here's the thing.

323
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,280
Mr. Xu,

324
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:43,880
I know you're busy,

325
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,960
but I can wait.

326
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,680
I'll wait right here in Beijing.

327
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,520
I see, Mr. Xuan.

328
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,360
Even though

329
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,480
I'm in charge of Xuan paper purchasing,

330
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:04,240
this isn't something we can settle

331
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,920
with just a few words between us.

332
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,360
Pine and Crane Studio has its own rules.

333
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,480
Give me a few days at least.

334
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:12,280
I'll invite experts to test the paper.

335
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,360
That's fair, right?

336
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:14,360
Of course, of course.

337
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:15,240
I understand, I understand.

338
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,240
Rules are rules.

339
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,760
Without rules, nothing can be achieved.

340
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,240
Let's leave it at that for now.

341
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,800
Leave me your number.

342
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,600
We'll be in touch.

343
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:24,520
Sure, sure.

344
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,680
Okay, thank you, thank you.

345
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,240
Where are you two heading?

346
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,680
Where are you off to?

347
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:39,880
Oh, right,

348
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:41,680
the files you assigned me this morning,

349
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:43,080
I've put them on your desk.

350
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,560
And Taozi's report is done too.

351
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,800
I sent it to you online.

352
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,560
Taozi's report isn't good enough.

353
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:49,880
She mixes up basic grammar,

354
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,200
and misuses punctuation.

355
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,320
I'll look at your materials when I'm back.

356
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:54,920
Probably not much better.

357
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,480
Are you two going to grab a meal?

358
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:58,240
When do we ever eat on time?

359
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:00,960
Fang Guangping's eco equipment needs upgrading.

360
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,240
We need to rush over there now.

361
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,520
The Environmental Bureau is sending people soon.

362
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:04,720
Doesn't one of you going suffice?

363
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:05,880
Come on, Director Liao,

364
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:08,240
just say what's on your mind.

365
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:12,240
Zhang Du wants to make Ancient-method paper.

366
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,880
He says he wants to create

367
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,920
the pure lineage of millennium-old Xuan paper.

368
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,680
I think this concept is excellent,

369
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,680
very high-minded.

370
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,800
And it fills a gap in Taohua Town's

371
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:25,000
Xuan paper industry.

372
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:28,040
It's a great direction for publicity.

373
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,520
That impressive, huh?

374
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:31,200
Lin Yiran,

375
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:34,480
he wants you to film and document it,

376
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,560
to promote his Ancient-method paper.

377
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,440
Honestly...

378
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,240
This Zhang Du...

379
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,560
Then of course I'll go!

380
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:41,720
My videos of him got millions of views.

381
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:43,400
Fine, you're amazing.

382
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,240
Go on, then.

383
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:44,960
Alright.

384
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,040
You go to Fang Guangping's place,

385
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:46,960
I'll go shoot the short video.

386
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:47,880
Go on, go on.

387
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,200
I'm off, Director Liao!

388
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,160
Ride carefully!

389
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,240
Leave it to me!

390
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,240
I'm off, bye!

391
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,880
You amateur,

392
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,240
do you even know how to drive?

393
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,560
Don't just shoot short videos,

394
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,120
write good articles for the channel too.

395
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:00,840
Don't worry!

396
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:01,480
Drive slowly!

397
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,160
Hello? Hello?

398
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:19,680
Yongnian.

399
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,000
How did the talks go?

400
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:26,280
How do you think they went?

401
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:30,720
The moment they heard it was the Xuan Family from Jing County, Anhui,

402
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:33,240
they were incredibly welcoming.

403
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,120
Serving tea, pouring water.

404
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,880
Don't you worry.

405
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,800
That's wonderful.

406
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:42,440
Now you've fulfilled your wish.

407
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:44,600
Beijing's a big place.

408
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:47,000
Running around like this, is your back okay?

409
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:49,040
Once it's done, hurry back home.

410
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,240
You think this is like buying a needle or a strip of cloth?

411
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:57,800
No matter what,

412
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,320
they have to follow the proper procedures.

413
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:01,560
They need someone to test the paper.

414
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,240
The paper hasn't been tested yet.

415
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,880
So the deal isn't sealed yet.

416
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,520
What is there to worry about with Xuan Family paper?

417
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:11,520
They'll get someone to test it, just a formality.

418
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,480
Once that formality's done,

419
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,520
I'll come right back.

420
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,040
It'll delay me at most,

421
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:19,080
maybe three to five days.

422
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:20,240
Alright, alright, alright.

423
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,760
I didn't mean to rush you.

424
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,320
Since you're already in Beijing,

425
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,880
you should get things settled properly.

426
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,440
Come back once everything's sorted out.

427
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:27,800
Alright, alright.

428
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:30,760
Xiumei, I've been tired all day.

429
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:32,080
Been negotiating all day, too.

430
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,000
I...

431
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,400
I want to turn in early.

432
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,480
Anyway, don't you worry.

433
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,440
Once it's done, I'll head back.

434
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,080
What's going on? Pulling a disappearing act?

435
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,760
You sure know how to enjoy yourself.

436
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,200
Off to find inspiration?

437
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,080
Find a spot to jump into the sea.

438
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,520
Getting far away is the right call.

439
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:42,240
Come on.

440
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:43,680
Come on.

441
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:44,880
Let's go.

442
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,400
Slow down.

443
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,320
Zhang Du.

444
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,400
How much farther?

445
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,880
Once we cross this mountain,

446
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:00,840
the water source is on top of the next one.

447
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,120
Another mountain?

448
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,000
I can't do it.

449
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:10,280
Xuan paper has lasted thousands of years

450
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:12,400
because every single detail matters.

451
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:15,000
The 108 steps of ancient papermaking,

452
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,120
each one must be perfect.

453
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:16,800
Zhang Du.

454
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,800
I think you're absolutely right.

455
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,520
But my lunch break is only two hours.

456
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,400
If we keep climbing, I won't make it back.

457
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:28,000
Come on, hang in there.

458
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:29,120
Let's go.

459
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,080
Slow down!

460
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,560
Let's just shoot here, okay?

461
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:37,280
Okay, okay, okay.

462
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,040
This scenery isn't great.

463
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,600
Let's find another spot.

464
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,040
Another spot?

465
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,840
Zhang Du, are you shooting scenery,

466
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:49,800
or introducing the water source?

467
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,800
I just want it to be more perfect.

468
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:54,920
Show the best scenery to our viewers.

469
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,840
That way, they'll be more interested

470
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:57,520
in ancient papermaking.

471
00:23:57,520 --> 00:23:58,800
Alright, okay, okay.

472
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,320
You go find one.

473
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,320
Don't rush to use it when you get home.

474
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:10,960
Find a cool, ventilated spot.

475
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,680
Don't do anything, just let it sit.

476
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,200
Let it settle.

477
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,760
In one to three years,

478
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,960
it'll be even softer than now.

479
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:18,960
And it absorbs ink beautifully.

480
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,480
Then you can use it.

481
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:23,040
Natural bleeding, ink in five shades.

482
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,680
Now that's authentic.

483
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,080
Alright then.

484
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,320
I'll do as you say.

485
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:28,760
No problem, trust me.

486
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:29,840
Satisfaction guaranteed.

487
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:31,040
Alright.

488
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:31,800
Thank you.

489
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,720
Take care now.

490
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,480
You're amazing.

491
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:37,800
You said it perfectly.

492
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:39,560
You really know your stuff.

493
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:40,480
You flatter me.

494
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,080
So, looking to buy paper?

495
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:43,520
Come, take a look.

496
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:44,680
Feel free to browse.

497
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,680
Just let me know if you need anything.

498
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:52,920
Just say what's on your mind.

499
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:53,680
About this...

500
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,400
You can take a look.

501
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,480
Xuan Family Paper.

502
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:07,720
No fancy names, just pure quality.

503
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:18,840
Good paper.

504
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,440
Authentic top-grade Xuan paper.

505
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,440
Truly rare.

506
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:25,240
It's rare for me to meet a true expert.

507
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:28,080
May I ask,

508
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:31,080
if this paper were sold here,

509
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:32,800
would it make the cut?

510
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:36,040
That's not up to me.

511
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:38,320
I don't have the final say.

512
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,000
Just give me an honest answer.

513
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,760
Compared to other papers,

514
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,280
how does it stack up?

515
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,560
Let me put it this way.

516
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,160
I'm just here to sell paper.

517
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,040
I can't speak out of turn.

518
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,480
Just tell me the truth.

519
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,680
What are you afraid of?

520
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:58,520
Sir,

521
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:00,800
you're coming in like clockwork.

522
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,600
Once in the morning, once in the afternoon.

523
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,960
There's really no need.

524
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:06,840
Our Manager Xu

525
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:09,080
has really been busy lately.

526
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,720
He rarely comes by.

527
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,680
I know, I know.

528
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,280
No rush, no rush.

529
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,160
I... I can wait.

530
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,240
It's been four days.

531
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:53,400
Coming by morning and afternoon,

532
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,120
just refusing to leave.

533
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:08,720
Mr. Xuan.

534
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:11,720
Hello, Mr. Xu.

535
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,880
Come eat in my office, alright?

536
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,320
No need, no need.

537
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,680
I'll just eat here.

538
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:18,880
Let me pour you some hot water.

539
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,080
Thank you, thank you.

540
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:21,440
Here, here.

541
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:24,760
Please, have a seat.

542
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,440
Thank you, Manager Xu.

543
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:29,120
Sit, sit, sit.

544
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:36,920
It's been four days now.

545
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:38,080
You haven't gone back.

546
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:39,400
Coming here every day.

547
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:45,840
The matter isn't settled.

548
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,120
I can't just go back.

549
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:56,520
I see, Mr. Xuan.

550
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:59,200
There's an expert, a master.

551
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:02,200
He often comes by these years,

552
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,120
just searching for a good paper.

553
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,120
Let me contact him,

554
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,320
and ask him to test your paper.

555
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,520
If he says your paper is good,

556
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,520
then we've cleared this hurdle.

557
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,680
Wonderful, wonderful!

558
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,040
Right now,

559
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:19,520
I'll give Master Jiang Ziliu

560
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:20,600
a call.

561
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,160
Arrange a time with him.

562
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,120
Who did you say?

563
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,440
Jiang Ziliu.

564
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,320
The finest painter in the capital.

565
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:32,600
Manager Xu,

566
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:33,680
could you...

567
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:35,680
could you find another master?

568
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,520
Because...

569
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:38,880
he, he, he...

570
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:40,520
He's always searching for good paper.

571
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,320
You're afraid he's too picky, right?

572
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,200
That's not what I'm afraid of.

573
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,760
I'm afraid he won't understand.

574
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,720
He won't understand?

575
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:55,880
Mr. Xuan,

576
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:59,440
getting Master Jiang to test your paper,

577
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,840
I had to work up the nerve, you know?

578
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,520
If you're still going to nitpick,

579
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,400
then there's really nothing I can do.

580
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:07,280
Manager Xu,

581
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:08,480
I'm not picky, I'm not picky.

582
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,080
Please have him test the paper.

583
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,520
Have him test the paper.

584
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:14,040
Alright then, wait for my call.

585
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,200
Let me tell you something.

586
00:29:36,320 --> 00:29:38,520
Pure Ancient-method paper isn't always better.

587
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,680
I've made paper with old Xuan for decades.

588
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,920
Why do we keep improving it?

589
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,200
Because it saves labor,

590
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,400
and the overall quality goes up.

591
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,320
Ancient-method paper has lasted a thousand years.

592
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:51,840
There's a reason for that.

593
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:53,680
It depends on what you're after.

594
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:56,120
Alright.

595
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,600
Here, look, look, look.

596
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,840
This is the pulp you made.

597
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,160
Lots of impurities.

598
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,160
See that?

599
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,040
When we wash the material,

600
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,080
we hook up running water for a rinse cycle.

601
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:08,720
Compared to your traditional method,

602
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,040
the bagged material comes out cleaner.

603
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:11,000
Higher whiteness.

604
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,720
Impurities carry the cultural charm of paper too.

605
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:17,200
You can't just chase whiteness.

606
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:19,240
If you put it that way, there's no arguing.

607
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:23,160
Only tradition taken to the extreme can break through.

608
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:25,720
What I fear is having no distinction,

609
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,560
being neither here nor there.

610
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:39,720
Master Jiang.

611
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:40,680
Welcome, Master Jiang, welcome.

612
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,400
Welcome, Master Jiang, an honor to have you.

613
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:46,480
I've waited long and hard for this call.

614
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:49,280
Without good paper, how would I dare disturb you?

615
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,920
You'd better not disappoint me.

616
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:52,680
It's absolutely top-grade Xuan paper.

617
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,520
It's the very best we can offer.

618
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:55,840
Alright.

619
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:57,800
Let's give it a try then.

620
00:30:58,080 --> 00:30:58,840
If you'd be so kind.

621
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,520
Fine paper.

622
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,480
Truly fine paper.

623
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:05,000
New paper from the Xuan Family of Jing County.

624
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,760
But better than ten years ago.

625
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:10,200
Master Jiang, you're amazing!

626
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:14,000
I even hid the label on purpose.

627
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,840
One drop, one stroke, and you knew it all.

628
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,680
Brilliant, absolutely brilliant!

629
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:21,520
Good, good.

630
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:24,080
All right, put it away, put it away.

631
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,040
Come, come, come.

632
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,080
Auntie Xu.

633
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:23,520
Miss Lin, you're here.

634
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:24,520
Did you need something?

635
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,560
Not really.

636
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,840
I just want you to join me for a meal.

637
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:30,400
Early this morning,

638
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,760
I went to the market and bought river shrimp.

639
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:32,760
Really fresh.

640
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:34,040
I also got some stovetop crispy rice.

641
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:34,520
I'll cook it all for you.

642
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,480
No, that's too much trouble.

643
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:37,840
It's no trouble.

644
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:39,520
Your Uncle Xuan isn't home anyway.

645
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,880
Come inside and keep me company.

646
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:43,800
I was just about to ask.

647
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,520
How are things going with Uncle Xuan?

648
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,440
I was just about to tell you.

649
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,080
They tested the paper.

650
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:55,120
And thought it was excellent.

651
00:33:55,920 --> 00:33:57,120
Talk about coincidence.

652
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:59,440
The one testing was Jiang Ziliu.

653
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:02,680
Xuan Yan's master. You've met him.

654
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:08,480
It's actually quite an interesting story.

655
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:10,560
This Jiang Ziliu,

656
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:13,520
he's been coming to our house for over a decade.

657
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,199
Xuan Yan was still little back then.

658
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:17,080
He was always asking Uncle Xuan

659
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:19,560
for this kind of paper and that kind.

660
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:21,040
His demands were very high.

661
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:22,480
Really picky.

662
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:25,800
The two of them argued every time they met.

663
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,320
After arguing, they'd meet again.

664
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,600
And after meeting, they'd argue again.

665
00:34:29,719 --> 00:34:33,239
But he refused to look at anyone else's paper.

666
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:36,560
This time, he was the one praising it.

667
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:39,159
That proves he truly approves

668
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,360
of the paper Uncle Xuan makes.

669
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,920
Of course.

670
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,239
But still,

671
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,080
whether they can work together

672
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:48,760
depends on fate.

673
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:50,560
Master Ye.

674
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:53,440
I'd like you to help me make some fine paper.

675
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,560
We're already working with Pine and Crane Studio.

676
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:03,800
Isn't that fine enough?

677
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,480
Not enough.

678
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,240
I'm talking about Ancient-method paper.

679
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:09,280
Pure ancient method.

680
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:12,000
Every step identical to the ancients.

681
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,320
The paper we make will be exactly the same.

682
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:15,920
Maybe even better.

683
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:17,840
Exactly like the ancients?

684
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:19,200
You'll work yourself to death.

685
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:21,840
In this regard,

686
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,880
you're exactly like old Xuan.

687
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,240
Suffering for no reason.

688
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:26,920
Well, I'm not having it.

689
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:32,240
You can't discuss ice with a summer insect.

690
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:34,760
If you want to do archaeology,

691
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,000
go dig up graves.

692
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,040
This is a paper mill.

693
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:38,520
Little Yu.

694
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,480
Master Zhang is kindly teaching you.

695
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,800
So learn properly.

696
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:42,440
Exactly.

697
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:43,480
My master isn't dead yet.

698
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:44,640
I don't need him teaching me.

699
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,000
Watch your mouth.

700
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:48,040
He's the heir now, the Second-in-command.

701
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,920
With master away, he calls the shots.

702
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,440
I can put up with a lot of things,

703
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,440
but I refuse to bow down to him.

704
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:54,440
Always going on about "ancient method."

705
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,200
Has he seen how the ancients made paper?

706
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:57,960
Tell him to go down there and ask them.

707
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:59,160
Then come back and tell me, okay?

708
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:12,640
Everyone,

709
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,680
you must be wondering

710
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:16,400
why I created this group chat.

711
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,000
I don't mean anything by it.

712
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,320
Tomorrow's our day off,

713
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,240
and I'd like to treat everyone to a meal.

714
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,160
So we can discuss things together.

715
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:26,040
After all, there's still a lot

716
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:27,960
I need to learn from all of you.

717
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,640
Please, do come.

718
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:31,880
And share your wisdom.

719
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,240
I'll book the restaurant right away

720
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:35,840
and send the address to the group.

721
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,520
If there's anything you'd like to eat,

722
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:38,880
just say so.

723
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,040
Don't be shy with me.

724
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:41,880
We're all family here.

725
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:48,600
Brother Zhang Du, I've got plans tomorrow.

726
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,640
I can't make it. I'm busy.

727
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,640
If those two aren't going, I'm not either.

728
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:55,280
What could you possibly treat us to anyway?

729
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:47,440
Xuan Yan made it.

730
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:50,200
Do you know how much it sells for?

731
00:37:50,720 --> 00:37:51,520
How much?

732
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:54,280
Nine hundred ninety-nine.

733
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:57,920
If it uses Qianlong Plum Blossom Jade Paper,

734
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,040
don't let its size fool you,

735
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:01,000
it's worth every penny.

736
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:08,800
Mr. Xuan, please have some tea.

737
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:10,800
No need, thank you, thank you.

738
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,280
Mr. Xuan, I really do owe you an apology.

739
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,440
Master Jiang had nothing but praise.

740
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:20,680
Kept singing its praises.

741
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,160
Said it's fine paper, top-quality paper.

742
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:27,480
But when I reported to the boss,

743
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:29,520
the boss asked me one question.

744
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:32,720
The sample paper you sent is good,

745
00:38:33,480 --> 00:38:34,440
but how can we be sure

746
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,640
future shipments will be just as good?

747
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:40,640
Manager Xu, you have my absolute word on that.

748
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:41,520
We always...

749
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:42,920
Please, sit, sit, sit.

750
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:44,760
Here's the thing.

751
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:48,280
We've been burned on this many times over the years.

752
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:50,040
Everyone who came was just like you,

753
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:51,480
looking honest and sincere,

754
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:53,080
and the paper they brought was excellent.

755
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,600
But once the contract was signed

756
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:55,440
and the deposit collected,

757
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:57,400
they'd turn around and change their tune.

758
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,360
Manager Xu,

759
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:00,680
the Xuan Family's partnership with Pine and Crane Studio

760
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,920
has always been built on trust.

761
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:05,280
That was a hundred years ago.

762
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:09,000
The losses happened in recent years.

763
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:11,840
Mr. Xuan,

764
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:17,480
we've been once bitten, twice shy.

765
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,720
Why do we prefer working with big factories?

766
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,120
That's exactly the reason.

767
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:25,920
We don't want to ruin the Pine and Crane Studio name.

768
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:32,640
Mr. Xuan, I really did my best on this.

769
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:34,400
You... you saw it all yourself.

770
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:39,520
Any more, and you're just putting me in a tough spot.

771
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:45,560
Uncle Xuan,

772
00:39:46,160 --> 00:39:48,200
Didn't you say the paper trial went well?

773
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:48,880
What happened?

774
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:51,240
The paper trial itself went smoothly.

775
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:52,400
But...

776
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:56,680
they just don't want to work with us.

777
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:59,480
The reason is they think our mill is too small.

778
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,600
They're worried the product quality

779
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:03,520
can't be guaranteed down the road.

780
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:04,640
I see.

781
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:05,600
So the problem is

782
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,600
Pine and Crane Studio doesn't trust us.

783
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:10,480
Then how about we invite them

784
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:12,360
to come and inspect our place?

785
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,680
Let them see how we make our paper,

786
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,000
and get to know

787
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,680
the reputation of Xuan Family Paper Mill.

788
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:20,160
I've already thought of that,

789
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:23,400
but I'm afraid it won't work.

790
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:26,360
After all, we haven't worked together in a hundred years.

791
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,640
There's no foundation of trust.

792
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:31,320
That's true.

793
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:33,560
Old Xuan,

794
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:37,160
that Jiang Ziliu,

795
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:39,840
didn't you say Jiang Ziliu

796
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,640
is a big shot in Beijing?

797
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:44,080
His word must carry weight.

798
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,600
Why don't you go see him?

799
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:46,440
How about it?

800
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:48,920
Jiang Ziliu...

801
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:51,920
He...

802
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,360
I think

803
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:55,560
Jiang Ziliu keeps coming to your home,

804
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:56,520
not anyone else's.

805
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,640
That's clear proof

806
00:40:57,640 --> 00:40:59,280
he approves of our paper.

807
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:01,920
And he spoke so highly of it during the trial.

808
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:02,640
I think if you go to him,

809
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:03,960
he'll definitely help out.

810
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:04,920
Exactly.

811
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:07,080
But Jiang Ziliu is even more stubborn than me.

812
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,200
He has to be in control of everything.

813
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:11,680
And back then, the two of us

814
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:13,000
even flipped the table on each other.

815
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,960
You can't blame him for that.

816
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,600
You were the one in the wrong first.

817
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:21,680
What did Uncle Xuan say back then?

818
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,560
He said he was bullshit and knew nothing.

819
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:26,560
Isn't that right?

820
00:41:27,640 --> 00:41:29,520
Uncle Xuan, just for that one remark,

821
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:30,920
you need to apologize to him.

822
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,840
I will absolutely not apologize to him.

823
00:41:33,960 --> 00:41:34,560
Then how about this?

824
00:41:34,720 --> 00:41:35,680
You don't apologize,

825
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:36,120
but

826
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,680
just tell him about the situation.

827
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:39,320
See what he does. Okay?

828
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:42,320
Old Xuan,

829
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:44,440
we finally made it to Beijing.

830
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,880
Whether it works out or not,

831
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:48,000
it doesn't matter.

832
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:49,600
But you and Jiang Ziliu

833
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:52,160
go back decades, after all.

834
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:54,120
Since we've come all this way,

835
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,680
we should at least go visit him.

836
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:56,840
Isn't that the right thing to do?

837
00:41:58,040 --> 00:42:00,640
Uncle Xuan, go see him right now.

838
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:02,760
We'll be waiting here for your news.

839
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:06,720
Let me think about it.

840
00:42:10,080 --> 00:42:10,640
I'm hanging up.

841
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:11,680
No more talking to him.

842
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:13,680
I'm hanging up then, Uncle Xuan.

843
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:30,680
Xiaoxue

844
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:33,440
This gentleman is here to see Mr. Jiang.

845
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:34,640
May I ask who you are?

846
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:37,560
I'm Xuan Yongnian from Jing County, Xuancheng, Anhui.

847
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:39,560
So you're Master Xuan.

848
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,360
Yes, yes, yes.

849
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,640
My dad mentions you often.

850
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:44,520
Is your dad home?

851
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:45,520
Yes, he is.

852
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:48,840
But I'm sorry,

853
00:42:48,840 --> 00:42:50,600
my dad is taking his afternoon nap right now.

854
00:42:51,520 --> 00:42:52,800
Then I won't disturb him.

855
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:54,280
I'll just wait for him here.

856
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:55,600
No need, Master Xuan.

857
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,200
Let me take you to the tea room.

858
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:58,200
You can sit and wait there.

859
00:42:58,200 --> 00:42:59,000
Alright, alright.
